{"symbol": "CD28", "uniprot": "P10747", "protein_name": "T-cell-specific surface glycoprotein CD28", "length": 220, "function": "Receptor that plays a role in T-cell activation, proliferation, survival and the maintenance of immune homeostasis (PubMed:1650475, PubMed:7568038). Functions not only as an amplifier of TCR signals but delivers unique signals that control intracellular biochemical events that alter the gene expression program of T-cells (PubMed:24665965). Stimulation upon engagement of its cognate ligands CD80 or CD86 increases proliferation and expression of various cytokines in particular IL2 production in both CD4(+) and CD8(+) T-cell subsets (PubMed:12196291, PubMed:1650475, PubMed:35397202). Mechanistically, ligation induces recruitment of protein kinase C-theta/PRKCQ and GRB2 leading to NF-kappa-B activation via both PI3K/Akt-dependent and -independent pathways (PubMed:21964608, PubMed:24665965, PubMed:7568038). In conjunction with TCR/CD3 ligation and CD40L costimulation, enhances the production of IL4 and IL10 in T-cells (PubMed:8617933)", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000178562", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.2233, "protein_drug": 0.692, "rna_drug": 0.472}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": false, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "Small molecule", "winning_axis": "protein", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.884", "sirna_score": "0.244", "aso_score": "0.378"}, "modality": "Small molecule", "structure": "data/structures/CD28.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.447, "volume": 275.3, "residues": [174, 175, 178, 179, 182]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.206, "volume": 440.8, "residues": [175, 176, 179, 180, 183, 184, 187]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.056, "volume": 239.0, "residues": [158, 159, 162, 163, 166]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/P10747"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "ht